definitions.definition: A widely diffused vegetable substance, found especially in seeds , bulbs and tubers , as extracted (e.g. from potatoes , corn , rice , etc.) in the form of a white, glistening, granular or powdery substance, without taste or smell, and giving a very peculiar creaking sound when rubbed between the fingers. It is used as a food, in the production of commercial grape sugar, for stiffening linen in laundries, in making paste, etc.
Carbohydrates , as with grain and potato based foods .
Any of various starch-like substances used as a laundry stiffener .

main_definition: ( uncountable ) A widely diffused vegetable substance, found especially in seeds , bulbs and tubers , as extracted (e.g. from potatoes , corn , rice , etc.) in the form of a white, glistening, granular or powdery substance, without taste or smell, and giving a very peculiar creaking sound when rubbed between the fingers. It is used as a food, in the production of commercial grape sugar, for stiffening linen in laundries, in making paste, etc.
secondary_definitions: ( nutrition , countable ) Carbohydrates , as with grain and potato based foods .
( uncountable ) A stiff , formal manner; formality .
( countable ) Any of various starch-like substances used as a laundry stiffener .
